<div class='commentinfo comment_comment'>
2008-10-08 03:14:29 (2061 days ago)
<div id='contact-1'>x (1)</div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Please explain how a 1-mile stretch of river can have average gradient of 100 FPM and maximum<br/>
gradient of 500 FPM. Maximum gradient figures cited 'up top' should always be computed across a<br/>
full mile, otherwise they are meaningless. If you wish to convey that some shorter portion has<br/>
steeper gradient, you may express that within the text of the description (as &quot;the river drops 50<br/>
feet in a quarter mile, for an effective gradient of 200 FPM&quot;) but that should NOT be in the<br/>
'Maximum Gradient' area. </div>
</td>
